  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Before you begin...</strong></p><p>This recipe takes around 5 -10 min<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>to prep, so get your casserole dish and all your ingredients ready, then wash your fruit and veg</p><p>Note: Make sure your dish is oven-proof and safe to use on the hob. Don't have one? Start cooking in a large, wide-based pan then transfer to an oven-proof dish and cover tightly with foil</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1718105998702-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1718105998702-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1718105998702-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1718105998702-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1718105998702-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Now, let's get started!</strong></p><p>Before you start cooking, take your <strong>chicken</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air, preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7 and boil a kettle</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based, <strong>hob-safe oven-proof casserole dish </strong>with a matching lid with a knob of <strong>butter </strong>over a medium-high heat</p><p>Chop your<strong> potatoes </strong>(skins on) into bite-sized pieces and add to the dish</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1718105992990-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1718105992990-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1718105992990-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1718105992990-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1718105992990-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Top, tail and slice your <strong>leek[s]</strong> into rounds, then wash thoroughly to remove any grit</p><p>Add the <strong>sliced leek</strong> to the potatoes with 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span><strong> flour</strong>, give everything a good mix up and cook for 30 secs</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1718106006093-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1718106006093-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1718106006093-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1718106006093-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1718106006093-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your<strong> chicken stock mix</strong> to the dish with<strong> </strong>350ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[450ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[600ml] </span><strong>boiled water</strong>, your <strong>Dijon mustard</strong>, the juice of <strong>half </strong>your <strong>lemon[s]</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Stir it all together and bring to the boil</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1718106010651-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1718106010651-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1718106010651-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1718106010651-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1718106010651-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add your <strong>chicken thighs</strong> (skin-side up) to a<strong> tin foil</strong>-lined baking tray (or two!) with a pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong></p><p>Put the tray[s] on the bottom shelf of the oven for 25 min or until cooked through (no pink meat!) and the skin is crispy</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1718106019299-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1718106019299-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1718106019299-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1718106019299-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1718106019299-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>At the same time, put the dish with the potatoes and leek into the oven, covered, for 25 min or until everything’s bubbling and the potatoes are almost tender</p><p>Use this time to clear up, set the table, have a cup of tea or simply chill!</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
